#### Step 4: Use the Content Provider

Now, you can use your Content Provider to perform operations on your list of books.

```java
// Insert a book
ContentValues values = new ContentValues();
values.put(BookContract.COLUMN_TITLE, "Sample Book");
values.put(BookContract.COLUMN_AUTHOR, "John Doe");
Uri newBookUri = getContentResolver().insert(BookContract.CONTENT_URI, values);

// Query all books
Cursor cursor = getContentResolver().query(BookContract.CONTENT_URI,
        new String[]{BookContract.COLUMN_ID, BookContract.COLUMN_TITLE, BookContract.COLUMN_AUTHOR},
        null,
        null,
        null);

// Update a book
Uri bookUri = ContentUris.withAppendedId(BookContract.CONTENT_URI, bookId);
values.put(BookContract.COLUMN_TITLE, "Updated Title");
getContentResolver().update(bookUri, values, null, null);

// Delete a book
getContentResolver().delete(bookUri, null, null);
